titleStmt.title: Midd. At the generall quarter sessions of the peace, of our Sovereign Lord the King, held for the County of Middlesex at Westminster in the said county, upon [...] next after the feast of Easter, (to wit) the [...] day of [...] in the year of the reign of our Sovereign Lord Charles the Second, by the grace of God, King of England, Scotland, France, and Ireland, defender of the faith, &c. the [...]. The rates of servants, wages, labourers, workmen and artificers, (in pursuance of the statute of the fifth of Queen Elizabeth, in that behalf made and provided) are rated and assessed by the Justices of the Peace of the said county....
titleStmt.author: Middlesex (England)
